description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an ideal and exciting post for a dietitian who has had some experience in Diabetes and paediatrics. The role will cover both adults and paediatric diabetes patients .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by 2 senior Dietitians in both Adults and Paediatrics.The role will involve being part of the Adult Diabetes Team and Paediatric Diabetes Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will involve both inpatient and outpatient work and support and training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although this role is advertised as a Band 6 , we would be happy to consider a Band 5 with an interest in diabetes / paediatrics , where we will alter the role to a development post,from which the current postholder was successful in completing . Full training will be given to the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is based at Broomfield Hospital , Chelmsford , Essex. Chelmsford is a busy vibrant City in the centre of Essex with its beautiful coastline and country parks, yet only 35 minutes from London on a direct train.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a team of 23 dietitians and excellent support from a full time secretary. We have access to funded CPD and have regular staff meetings dedicated to CPD and business matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBridget LeeJob titleDeputy Manager Nutrition and Dietetics / ASD DiabetesEmail addressbridget.lee@meht.nhs.ukTelephone number01245 516809Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also contact Harnom Zubairu on harnom.zubairu@meht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
